args: Did you hear about how Aeleen drove all\nthose villains away with just a glare?
Hear it? I SAW it! She had crazy eyes,\nso she did. I've never seen the like!
I don't wanna take my medicine!
If you don't, Aeleen will make you!
EEEEK! I'll take it! I'll taaaake it!
Yep. Sounds like Aeleen is REAL\npopular in that village.
Not sure popular is the word I'd use.

But it ain't like they hate her, exactly.
I mean, there's worse things to be than
the ＂nurse of nightmares＂ what ya don't
wanna be pissin' off.
I doubt she feels the same.
I can't believe that's how people are\ntalking about what happened.
Though I probably shouldn't be surprised;\nit's normal to be shocked by what I did.\nI mean, I'm rather shocked myself.
*sigh* I need to go to the village to do\nmy usual rounds, but I just...
Maybe I should take a day off.
Do you have a moment, Aeleen?
Yes, of course. What is it?
Sorry for showing up unannounced.\nAre you busy?
It's fine. How can I help?
Well, when I was training with Ranzal\nyesterday, I fell and hit my arm.
Goodness, that's a serious bruise!\nYou should have shown me this earlier.

It honestly didn't seem so bad yesterday,
but when I woke up this morning, it was...
Well, let's call it colorful. Anyway, do you
think you can take a look at it?
You really need to take better care\nof yourself, you know?

Yeah, I know. I've always been bad about
tending to myself ever since I was a kid.
Zethia used to take care of me like you're
doing now.
Yes. She would follow me everywhere,\ninsisting it was her job to heal me.
I suppose everyone dreams of being able\nto help others when they're young.
Maybe so. Speaking of which,\nwas that what made you want\nto be a nurse to begin with?
My hometown is far to the north,\nin a region of heavy snow.
We didn't have anyone who knew\nthe first thing about healing magic.
So when the roads were blocked by\nsnow—which happened often—getting\nsick or injured often spelled death.
Snow is always pretty from a distance,\nbut it's easy to forget how hard it can be\nfor the people who live with it.
You're right about that. But one day,\na nurse came from out of town.
She built a small hospital for us\nthat changed everything.
She was kind, devoted, and always happy.\nSoon, illness was no longer the death\nsentence it used to be.
I looked up to her, and dreamed of\nbeing like that one day myself.
And that set you down this path?
It's almost too straightforward a reason.
Still, as much as I want to be like her,\nit seems that will never happen.
Because at the slightest provocation,\nI turn into my other self—as with\nthose bandits the other day.
Our nurse was the embodiment of\nkindness, but I never will be.
I think you're doing perfectly fine.
Did you not see how horrified everyone\nwas at my actions?
They will never think of me as a\nkindly healing goddess now.
Aeleen, did you look up to that nurse\njust because you wanted to be a\n＂kindly healing goddess＂?
I don't think that's the case.
I think it was because she helped lift the\nspecter of death that hung over your\nvillage and its people.
You might not be able to become exactly\nlike that nurse—but that's because you're\nNOT her. People are all different.
But even if you don't have her personality,\nisn't it enough to become a nurse who\nhelps people as she did?
All this time, I've been so focused on\nbecoming her that I lost sight of why I\nstarted feeling that way in the first place.
I need to focus on trying to be more like\nher in my deeds, not her doppelganger.
I know you can do it.
Thank you for helping me realize\nall of this, Prince {player_name}.
Some people from a nearby village came\nto inquire about why their usual nurse\nhadn't come to visit. They're quite worried.
They're waiting outside the gate.\nWould you mind going to see them?
It seems someone sees you the way\nyou saw the nurse from your childhood.
Er, by the way, I suppose I have no\nreason to keep this from you, so...
A few of the patients who came today\nseem to be rather...frightened.
They believe they have angered Aeleen,\nyet want her help so badly they practically\nbegged me to go find her.
Let's maybe not tell Aeleen that bit.
